    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "From the (new and improved) docstring for cut\r\n\r\n```\r\nbins : int, sequence of scalars, or pandas.IntervalIndex\r\n    The criteria to bin by.\r\n\r\n    * int : Defines the number of equal-width bins in the range of `x`. The\r\n      range of `x` is extended by .1% on each side to include the minimum\r\n      and maximum values of `x`.\r\n \r\n```\r\n\r\nSo your lowest bin is extended by 0.001.\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [31]: x.min() - 0.001 * (x.max() - x.min())\r\nOut[31]: -2.999\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you want to disable that you can provide the bins ahead of time, in which case no extending is done."
